1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
The Spiritual Planes is a social survival game where players take on the role of an Earthbound spirit navigating the afterlife's social structure. The core mechanic is discernment — identifying hidden entity types through behavioral tells, speech patterns, and energy shifts.
Key Differentiator: No emojis. No labels. No easy identifiers. Players must learn to "read" spirits the same way one reads people in real life — through observation, intuition, and pattern recognition.
Monetization: Free-to-play with premium cosmetics, story expansions, and spiritual guide subscriptions.
Target Launch: Q2 2027
2. GAME CONCEPT & CORE LOOP
2.1 The Premise
You are dead. You didn't make it to the next afterlife. You're stuck in the Spiritual Planes — a liminal space between life and the afterlife. Other spirits surround you. Some are allies. Some are predators. Some are wounded. Some are mimics. You must figure out who is who before the chaos consumes you.
2.2 The Core Loop
plain
ENTER SESSION → OBSERVE SPIRITS → INTERACT → IDENTIFY → SET BOUNDARIES → 
RESTORE OR RESIST → EARN FAITH/REDUCE CHAOS → ADVANCE PHASE → REPEAT
2.3 Session Structure
Duration: 10-20 minutes per session
Players: 1 human player + 4-6 AI spirits per session
Multiplayer: Up to 4 human players per shared session
Frequency: Unlimited sessions, with daily bonus for first 3
2.4 Win Condition
There is no "winning." There is only choosing:
Ascend: Move to the next afterlife (complete the game)
Stay: Remain as a guide for new spirits (endless mode)
Return: Go back to the living world as a guiding presence (premium story)
