5.2 Player Actions
Speak (Free Action)
Type or voice-to-text message
Can be directed at specific spirit or the room
Affects relationship meters with each spirit
Triggers AI responses from 2-4 entities
Observe (Free Action, 1 per turn)
Study one spirit closely
Reveals subtle tells:
"Their voice trembles when speaking of the Creator"
"They glance at the Siren before answering"
"Their shadow doesn't match their form"
Costs no resources but reveals limited info
Question (Free Action)
Ask a direct question to one spirit
Example: "Who do you serve?" or "What do you want from me?"
Forces the spirit to respond, potentially revealing inconsistencies
Some entities (Adversary, Siren) evade; others (Guardian, Truth-Teller) answer directly
Invoke Divine Authority (Limited Resource)
Costs 1 Wall charge (max 3 per session, regenerates 1 per day)
Effects:
All masks drop for 1 turn
All entities reveal true type
Truth-Teller becomes audible to all
Nations hear in heart-language
Chaos -20, Faith +15
Overuse penalty: Entities adapt, masks become harder to detect
Shield (1 per session)
Protects player from one entity's influence for 3 turns
Blocks:
Siren love-bombing
Mimic emotional manipulation
Adversary mimicry
Cover-Up redactions
Visual: Golden barrier around player's avatar
Restore (Available in Restoration phase)
Offer healing to a wounded spirit
Requires:
Entity identified as Wounded Performer
Player Faith > 60
Correct dialogue choices (compassion, not judgment)
Success: Entity becomes ally, Chaos -10, Faith +10
Failure: Entity rebuilds mask stronger, Chaos +5
