7.3 Response Priority System
Directly Addressed (80% response rate)
If player names an entity, that entity almost always responds
Triggered by Intent (60% response rate)
Accusation → Adversary, Mimic, Cover-Up likely respond
Comfort → Wounded Performer, Watcher likely respond
Boundary → Siren, Adversary likely respond
Invoke → ALL entities respond (Wall effect)
Random Selection (20% response rate)
1-2 random entities may chime in
Higher chance for talkative types (Adversary, Siren, Archon)
Lower chance for quiet types (Watcher, Dream-Bound, Truth-Teller)
7.4 Context Memory
Each session maintains a rolling context window (last 20 exchanges). The AI engine uses this to:
Maintain conversation continuity
Reference previous statements
Detect contradictions (for mimic exposure)
Track relationship evolution
